---
/**
 * consistent-hashing-deep-dive · Figure 7 — "PREFERENCE LIST: N distinct physical nodes".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source HTML (figure + svg + figcaption). Isolated as
 * an .astro component. It references marker-end="url(#arw)" (fill #6b675f); that
 * arrowhead marker was declared once in the source's top-of-body <svg defs> and
 * is inlined here in a local <defs> so the figure resolves standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 230"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Walking clockwise to N distinct physical nodes, skipping extra vnodes of an already-picked machine, ideally across distinct racks"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="300"
                y="20"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">PREFERENCE LIST — walk clockwise to N DISTINCT physical nodes</text
            >
            <circle cx="170" cy="130" r="84" fill="none" stroke="#6b675f" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle>
            <!-- key -->
            <circle cx="170" cy="46" r="5" fill="#1f3a5a"></circle><text
                x="170"
                y="36"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="9"
                fill="#1f3a5a">key k</text
            >
            <!-- vnodes around: label physical machine -->
            <circle cx="226" cy="74" r="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle><text x="248" y="70" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a">A (r1) ✓</text>
            <circle cx="254" cy="130" r="8" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle><text x="270" y="134" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417">A again ✗ skip</text>
            <circle cx="226" cy="186" r="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle><text x="248" y="190" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a">B (r2) ✓</text>
            <circle cx="114" cy="186" r="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle><text x="60" y="190" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a">C (r3) ✓</text>
            <circle cx="86" cy="130" r="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle>
            <circle cx="114" cy="74" r="8" fill="#f1eee2" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle>
            <!-- clockwise walk -->
            <path
                d="M 176 50 A 78 78 0 0 1 222 70"
                fill="none"
                stroke="#6b675f"
                stroke-dasharray="3 3"
                marker-end="url(#arw)"></path>
            <text x="170" y="125" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >N=3 replicas:</text
            >
            <text x="170" y="138" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#2f5d3a">A, B, C</text>
            <text x="170" y="151" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >distinct racks</text
            >
            <!-- right callout -->
            <g>
                <rect x="356" y="56" width="236" height="150" rx="9" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#7a1f12"
                ></rect>
                <text x="372" y="80" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                    >Why "distinct"?</text
                >
                <text x="372" y="100" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417"
                    >✗ skip extra vnodes of A — else all</text
                >
                <text x="372" y="113" font-size="9.5" fill="#9a2417"
                    >3 "replicas" land on machine A</text
                >
                <text x="372" y="129" font-size="9.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                    >✓ distinct physical nodes survive a</text
                >
                <text x="372" y="142" font-size="9.5" fill="#2f5d3a">single machine failure</text>
                <text x="372" y="158" font-size="9.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                    >✓ distinct racks / AZs survive a</text
                >
                <text x="372" y="171" font-size="9.5" fill="#2f5d3a">rack power loss</text>
                <text x="372" y="192" font-size="9.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
                    >This list = the set R+W&gt;N runs over</text
                >
            </g>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        This ordered list of distinct physical targets is Dynamo's <strong>preference list</strong> —
        exactly the set the <code>R + W &gt; N</code> quorum operates over.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
